## Automating Legal Filing Requirements

One of our solution providers created a custom solution for a client in a highly regulated industry with a lot of required paperwork. Not only do they have a multifaceted workflow, but also have many requirements that must be met at specific recurring deadlines  Some of these deadlines require collaborating with other individuals and require ongoing attention to ensure they are on track to meet those requirements.

When our solution provider met with them to design their custom, they discovered 19 separate types of deadlines they needed to maintain for more than a dozen individuals.

Before we signed on the client, they were doing everything by paper, and they were encountering a lot of challenges with the paperwork. It was difficult to track each of the different deadlines, and it was next to impossible to gain a bird’s-eye view of their processes. Their annual audits not only were time-consuming but also frequently uncovered clerical errors--understandable, given the vast complexity of the requirements.

Their custom solution allowed them to track these deadlines, ranking them from “urgent”, “upcoming”, and “eventual”. As soon as they entered the required documentation to clear a deadline, the solution would automatically create the next deadline. This not only automated their paper trail, but it eliminated the possibility of forgetting about one of those 19 deadlines.

Since implementing their solution, each audit has only uncovered very minor issues. It has allowed the client to cut costs by streamlining the day-to-day management and reducing the complexity of annual audits. Just as importantly, it has also helped them to establish their reputation as a careful, thorough team.
